external_knowledge:
- Significant voting populations refer to the number of people eligible to vote in the state; 
- Sizeable vote count in the 2020 presidential election implies more than 1 million votes;
- Arranged in order of their most significant voting populations means sorting the results in descending order based on the total voting population.

sql:
SELECT AVG(population) AS average_population
FROM states
WHERE region = 'East';

SELECT CAST(
    COUNT(CASE WHEN vt.voting_pop_2020 >= 10000000 THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS REAL
) * 100 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM states) AS percentage_states_with_voting_pop_10m
FROM voting_trends vt;

